criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Surgical indication of conservative or removal breast surgery, associated with
             axillary lymphadenectomy or sentinel lymph node biopsy

          -  Any type of breast cancer

          -  Age range over 18 years

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Breast cancer recurrence;

          -  Surgical treatment for bilateral breast cancer;

          -  Presence of lymphedema in the upper limb, measured by means of cirtometry of the upper
             limb with a measuring tape 14, asymmetries of more than 1.5 cm between the limbs were
             considered edema;

          -  Diagnosis of metastases;

          -  Shoulder pain compatible with shoulder compression symptoms as determined by the
             positive Hawkins-Kennedy test 30;

          -  Previous history of surgery and fractures in the upper extremities.
